TWO men were injured this morning following a shooting in a parking lot on Beyers Naude Road in Blackheath, Johannesburg.ER24 paramedics found the men lying on the ground, surrounded by police officersThree other men were arrested by the police following the shooting.However one man was shot on the leg and the second suspect was wounded on his face.Paramedics treated the patients and thereafter transported the patient with the gunshot wound, under law enforcement supervision, to a nearby hospital. The patient with the minor wounds declined transportation to a hospital.Details surrounding the incident are not clear at the moment, but local police are investigating the matter.